#: of numpy.polynomial.legendre.legadd:35
msgid ""
"Unlike multiplication, division, etc., the sum of two Legendre series is a "
"Legendre series (without having to \"reproject\" the result onto the basis "
"set) so addition, just like that of \"standard\" polynomials, is simply "
"\"component-wise.\""
msgstr ""

